<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 31 at 8:02AM CST  by NWS Huntsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Jackson
and southeastern Franklin Counties through 815 AM CST...
At 802 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bridgeport, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30 to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bridgeport, Stevenson, Anderson, Bass, Long Island and Russell Cave
National Monument.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
